      "side": 1,
      "message": "PAM and privilege mapping are independent.\nPAM authenticates the password against LDAP, it has no knowledge of OpenBMC\u0027s role map.\nGetUserInfo is a separate D-Bus call to phosphor-user-manager that resolves the user\u0027s privilege from the LDAP group-to-role mapping configured on the BMC.\nSince commit 395711d removed the default fallback to priv-user, a user can now have valid credentials but an empty UserPrivilege if no admin configured a role map for their LDAP group.\nPAM succeeding just means the password is correct.\nThe empty role is an authorization problem, not an authentication problem.",
      "parentUuid": "a6f2e24f_f16353e1",
